# End-of-session smoke

Before finishing any session that touched `apps/`, `scripts/`, infra, or Makefile:

```bash
make smoke
```

## Context

1. [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)
2. [docs/STATUS.md](../../docs/STATUS.md)
3. [docs/ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ROADMAP.md)

## After completing an issue

Run [end-task-workflow](./end-task-workflow.mdc):

- Linear → Done
- Update STATUS.md + ROADMAP.md

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `make smoke` | Stack + tests (stub grows with monorepo) |
| `make agent-verify` | Gate C |
| `make up` / `make down` | Start/stop (when configured) |

## On failure

Fix and re-run. Check logs under `.runtime/logs/` when stack exists.
